{{!--
  file.hbs — outermost wrapper applied to every emitted C# file.
  Wraps a pre-rendered inner declaration (class / interface / enum) with the
  file header, using directives, and namespace block.

  Override via tspconfig.yaml:
    options:
      "@massivescale/tsp-aspnetcore-api":
        templates:
          file: "./templates/file.hbs"

  ── Template variables ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  {{namespace}}   — fully-qualified C# namespace string, e.g. "Acme.Api.Models"

  {{usings}}      — array of namespace strings (already sorted: System.* first,
                    then alphabetically).  Iterate with {{#each usings}}.
                    Does NOT include the `using` keyword or trailing semicolons.

  {{body}}        — pre-rendered inner declaration produced by another template
                    (class.hbs, interface.hbs, or enum.hbs).  The body text
                    uses no leading indentation; pass it through {{indent body}}
                    to place it at 4 spaces inside the namespace block.

  {{fileName}}    — basename of the file being emitted, e.g. "Person.g.cs",
                    "IUser.g.cs", or "UsersControllerBase.g.cs".
                    Useful for adding a file-name comment in the header or
                    for conditional logic based on the output file name.

  ── Built-in helpers ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  {{indent <text>}}        — prefixes every non-empty line of <text> with 4
                             spaces; critical for placing the body declaration
                             inside the namespace block
  {{#if (isDefined val)}}  — true when val is not undefined

  ── Handlebars #each data ───────────────────────────────────────────────────

  Inside {{#each usings}}: @index, @first, @last, {{this}} = current namespace

  ── Common customisations ────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  • Add a copyright / licence banner before the auto-generated guard:
      // Copyright (c) Acme Corp 2025. All rights reserved.
      // <auto-generated/>

  • Replace the block namespace with a file-scoped namespace (C# 10+):
      namespace {{namespace}};
      {{indent body}}
      (remove the wrapping braces entirely)

  • Remove `#nullable enable` if the project sets <Nullable>enable</Nullable>
    in the .csproj and you want a clean diff.

  • Add analyser suppressions for generated-code warnings:
      #pragma warning disable CS8618
      {{indent body}}
      #pragma warning restore CS8618

  • Add the filename to the auto-generated header comment:
      // <auto-generated — {{fileName}}/>

  • Conditionally emit the usings section only when there are usings:
      {{#if usings}}
      {{#each usings}}using {{this}};
      {{/each}}
      {{/if}}
--}}
//-----------------------------------------------------------------------
// <copyright file="{{fileName}}" />
//
// This file is AUTO-GENERATED. Do not edit this file directly.
// <auto-generated />
//-----------------------------------------------------------------------
#pragma warning disable CS1591 // Missing XML comment for publicly visible type or member
#pragma warning disable CS0612 // Type or member is obsolete
#nullable enable

{{#each usings}}using {{this}};
{{/each}}
namespace {{namespace}}
{
{{indent body}}
}

#pragma warning restore CS0612 // Type or member is obsolete
#pragma warning restore CS1591 // Missing XML comment for publicly visible type or member